        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:56AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 256 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Jenny Lind, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Lavaca...                         Alma...
Shibley...                        Dyer...
Kibler...                         Greenwood...
Concord...                        Central City...
Figure Five...                    Mill Creek...
Rye Hill...                       Barling...
Fort Smith...                     Fort Smith Regional Airport...
Van Buren...                      Furry...
Jenny Lind...                     Rudy...
Bonanza...                        Arkoma...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 0 and 18.
Interstate 540 between mile markers 1 and 14.
Interstate 49 near mile marker 22.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
